name: Abhishek Mankuskar
bio:
I am a skilled developer and an Open Source Enthusiast, but I am also a community builder. As a Program Lead Manager at Socials Winter of Code (SWOC), I provided leadership to strategize, operate, and achieve the organization's goals. I was Leader in building and managing the entire project and website of SWOC, an Open Source Program.
I have also given lots of Online & Offline speaker sessions on Open Source and React.js in various colleges and communities.
I also joined Coditas as an Associate Software Engineer, where I learned and embraced the world of Frontend development using React.js and expanded his knowledge in areas like SASS, Clean Coding, Routes, Hooks, and Redux.

name: Bhavik Makwana
community_title: Google Developer Expert for Flutter & Dart
bio: Bhavik is working at multipl.xyz as a software engineer, a GDE for Flutter and Dart, Google certified associate android developer and an Open-source contributor. He is one of the early Flutter adopters and loves to share knowledge through blog posts, public speaking, and open source contributions. He has also started a community in Ahmedabad for Flutter and was featured in "The top 45 must-follow Flutter experts on Twitter" by codemagic.io.

name: Jaldeep Asodariya
bio: Jaldeep Asodariya is a seasoned Senior Mobile Engineer at HighLevel with a proven track record of developing cutting-edge Android and Flutter applications, earning high client satisfaction. He also serves as a Co-Organizer of the Google Developer Group (GDG) in Ahmedabad. Jaldeep's passion lies in IoT and Android Things, with a strong proficiency in Google Assistant application development and NodeJS. Jaldeep is a versatile and skilled professional in the tech industry.

bio: I am a software engineer passionate about building backend systems and creating DevOps pipelines. With a knack for community building, I enjoy sharing my knowledge through public speaking engagements and mentoring up-and-coming developers.

name: Pawan Kumar
community_title: Google Developer Expert for Firebase & Flutter
bio: Pawan Kumar is a Lead Engineer at Frontier and an Advocate for technology. With over 8 years of experience in mobile application development, he has honed his skills in a variety of technologies. He is highly recognized in the developer community and has been awarded as a Google Developer Expert for his expertise in Flutter and Firebase. Pawan has been able to establish a strong social media presence with over 125K subscribers on YouTube, 60K followers on LinkedIn, and 35K followers on Twitter. His contributions to open-source software have earned him a considerable following with over 10K followers on Github. With his vast experience and strong influence, Pawan is a highly valued asset to the technology community.

name: Sampath Kumar Balivada
bio: Sai Sampath Kumar Balivada is a seasoned Software Engineer at PayPal, based in Visakhapatnam, India. With a passion for crafting intuitive and engaging experiences, he specializes in ensuring transactional compliance across PayPal and its partners. Previously, he contributed significantly to Amazon Web Services (AWS), excelling in roles such as Cloud Support Associate. Sai Sampath holds a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science and Engineering and boasts certifications in AWS, Google Go programming, and open-source software development. As an organizer for GDG Vizag, he combines technical prowess with a commitment to community engagement, reflecting his dedication to both professional excellence and knowledge sharing.

name: Sasi Teja Kamsu
bio: Meet Sasi, an Engineer at Confluent, the visionary creators of Kafka. With a rich professional journey that includes roles at AWS and Cisco, Sasi is a seasoned expert in Kafka, Cloud technologies, and DevOps. He excels in designing and implementing real-time data streaming applications. A certified AWS Solutions Architect Associate, Sasi's passion for data science and machine learning is evident through a research paper in time series analytics. A dedicated community enthusiast, he's been an integral part of the GDG (Google Developer Groups) community since 2018

name: Santosh Nimmani
bio: Santhosh Nimmani's story is one of remarkable personal growth. Growing up in a small town, he faced challenges as an introvert with communication difficulties. Despite being an average student, he decided to overcome these obstacles. In college, he discovered his passion for extracurricular activities, gaining confidence and leadership skills. After landing a job in IT, he faced the challenge of transitioning from a non-computer science background. A personal setback left him in a state of loneliness and self-doubt, but he found hope through exercise, connecting with people who didn't know his past, and learning public speaking. Santhosh now shares his experiences through empowering videos, helping others while improving his own skills. His journey from an introverted small-town boy to a confident TEDx speaker, author of the Amazon Best Seller book "Rise of the Proud Introverts" , India's First Proud Introverts Career Mentor, and software professional is a testament to resilience and self-discovery, inspiring others to overcome their own obstacles.

name: Vasanth Korada
